{"type":"message","id":"32094400","parentId":"ce1891eb","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:34:54.883Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The morning news state file actually EXISTS and shows:\n- last_success_at: 2026-04-03 08:52:22\n- The report was generated and pushed to Feishu successfully\n- The push was via Feishu with message ID om_x100b53c4baa538a4c11fea9695d0864\n\nBut the mainline health guard is still showing it as MISSING. The issue is likely that the health guard script is checking for a different state file path, not this one.\n\nThe health report says `status: \"MISSING\" | last_success: \"None\"` for morning news, but the actual state file shows it was generated at 08:52:22 today and pushed successfully.\n \nSo the real problem is a path mismatch—the guard is probably looking in the wrong location for the state file, while the actual generation and push completed fine. The cron job search confirms there are no morning-related jobs configured, which is why the health check is reporting it as missing.\n\nLooking at the state file, it shows \"report_fix_note\": \"state repaired after push command-not-found failure\" and \"deadline_alert\" with \"ok: false\" due to a node environment issue. Since the morning news was successfully generated and pushed to Feishu, this is a monitoring problem rather than an actual execution failure. The guard's check script seems to be using a different file path than what's actually being used. I should report that the morning news actually succeeded—the real issue is just the monitoring mismatch.\n\nNow I'm noticing there are several missing items flagged in the health check beyond just the morning news. Let me check if the markdown file was actually created to confirm the success.","thinkingSignature":"8ad2555519b55c9bfc11ae93765373a3c4e8ea6f6c23028c7a77e452f8921ea5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dim0hudmpaap_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /Users/ling/.